From 08ab72f2d195d1e9fb765bb05db7091a4a7cc527 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Basil Goff <shawn7400@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 11:00:18 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Persist Context Bonsai message metadata through parsing
 and storage

Context Bonsai needs message metadata to survive parsing and session storage so archived anchors and restore markers remain available across later turns. v1.17.13 moved message persistence to an event-sourced projector, so this adds the optional metadata field to the User and Assistant message schemas (the projector already round-trips the field through MessageTable) and a MessageV2.update helper that verifies the message exists, rewrites its stored row, and republishes MessageUpdated so subscribers and the durable projector converge on the same payload. Focused message-v2 and session tests cover the decode and storage round-trip against the current runtime APIs.

Re-implemented from commit 712175fd95d2923c91e082c1c02708d648832cdd

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
