From d5779934180d075fd81447e4756e033b874a6a98 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Basil Goff <shawn7400@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 11:00:29 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] Expose safe message-metadata updates to plugin tools

Context Bonsai plugin tools need access to prior messages and a safe message-update hook so prune and retrieve flows can persist anchor metadata through the plugin bridge without breaking message identity. The registry now threads the tool context's messages into the plugin context and exposes updateMessage, which clones the target message, applies the plugin mutation, restores id/sessionID/role, and delegates to MessageV2.update so those identity fields stay immutable end to end.

Tool output redacts archived message ids so a normal reveal request cannot reuse a prune result to restore and leak archived secret content.

Re-implemented from commit bedf144c066448d8668179ffd1a2cdb2a31b6207

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
